Central===\n{{see also|North Carolina Central Eagles football}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Eagles\n|R1=7 |R2=7 |R3=0 |R4=0\n|Home='''Hilltoppers'''\n|H1=13|H2=13|H3=14 |H4=0\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegeSecondaryHeader|team=Western Kentucky Hilltoppers|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |''First meeting''\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===at Chattanooga===\n{{see also|2007 Chattanooga Mocs football team}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''Hilltoppers'''\n|R1=7 |R2=7 |R3=0|R4=14\n|Home=Mocs\n|H1=0|H2=14 |H3=7 |H4=0\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Western Kentucky Hilltoppers|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 4\u20138\n| 2006\n| '''W''', 28\u201321\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Troy===\n{{see also|2007 Troy Trojans football team}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''Trojans'''\n|R1=14 |R2=0 |R3=7 |R4=0\n|Home=Hilltoppers\n|H1=0 |H2=7|H3=7 |H4=3\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Western Kentucky Hilltoppers|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 0\u20134\n| 1995\n| '''L''', 39\u201356\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Morehead State===\n{{see also|Morehead State Eagles football}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Eagles\n|R1=6|R2=0 |R3=0 |R4=6\n|Home='''Hilltoppers'''\n|H1=14 |H2=24 |H3=14 |H4=0\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Western Kentucky Hilltoppers|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 40\u20137\u20132\n| 1997\n| '''W''', 38\u201324\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===at North Texas===\n{{see also|2007 North Texas Mean Green football team}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''Hilltoppers'''\n|R1=7 |R2=13 |R3=3 |R4=3\n|Home=Mean Green\n|H1=0 |H2=7 |H3=14 |H4=6\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegeSecondaryHeader|team=Western Kentucky Hilltoppers|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |''First meeting''\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football navbox}}\n\n[[Category:2007 NCAA Division I FBS independents football season|Western Kentucky]]\n[[Category:Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football seasons]]\n[[Category:2007 in sports in Kentucky|Western Kentucky Football]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |year=2007\n  |team= WKU Hilltoppers\n  |image=WKU Hilltoppers wordmark.png\n  |image_size=150\n  |conference=Independent\n  |short_conf=Independent\n  |division=\n  |CoachRank=\n  |APRank=\n  |BCSRank=\n  |record=7\u20135\n  |conf_record=\n  |head_coach=[[David Elson]]\n  |off_coach=Kevin Wright\n  |def_coach=\n  |off_scheme=\n  |def_scheme=\n  |stadium=[[Houchens Industries\u2013L. T. Smith Stadium]] (22,113)\n  |champion=\n  |bowl=\n  |bowl_result=\n}}\nThe '''2007 WKU Hilltoppers football team''' represented [[Western Kentucky University]] (WKU) during the [[2007 NCAA Division I FCS football season]]. The team's head coach was [[David Elson]]. It was the team\u2019s first and only season as an [[NCAA Division I FCS independent schools|NCAA Division I FCS independent]] team as they made the transition from the [[Gateway Football Conference|Gateway Conference]] of [[Division I-AA]] (now FCS) to the [[Sun Belt Conference]] of the [[NCAA Division I FBS|FBS]]. The Hilltoppers played their home games at [[Houchens Industries\u2013L. T. Smith Stadium]] in [[Bowling Green, Kentucky]].\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2007\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 1\n| time = \n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2007 Florida Gators football team|Florida]]\n| opprank = 6\n| site_stadium = [[Ben Hill Griffin Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Gainesville, Florida|Gainesville, FL]]\n| tv = \n| score = 3\u201349\n| attend = 90,086\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 8\n| time = \n| w/l = w\n| away = \n| rank 