n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = TV series \n| director        = Yoshiyuki Fujiwara\n| producer        = DMM.futureworks\n| writer          = Yoshiyuki Fujiwara<br>Jin Tanaka\n| music           = \n| studio          = [[Doga Kobo]]\n| licensee        = \n| network         = [[TV Asahi]], [[AbemaTV]], [[TV Asahi|BS Asahi]]\n| first           = April 4, 2020\n| last            = \n| episodes        = 18\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Sing \"Yesterday\" for Me'''''|\u30a4\u30a8\u30b9\u30bf\u30c7\u30a4\u3092\u3046\u305f\u3063\u3066|Iesutadei o Utatte}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series by [[Kei Toume]]. It began serialization in [[Shueisha]]'s [[seinen manga|''seinen'' manga]] magazine ''[[Business Jump]]'' in 1997, and it moved to Shueisha's ''[[Grand Jump]]'' magazine in November 2011 until it ended in June 2015. It was collected in eleven ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes. An [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[Doga Kobo]] premiered on April 4, 2020.\n\n==Characters==\n===Main Characters===\n;{{Nihongo|Rikuo Uozumi|\u9b5a\u4f4f \u9678\u751f|Uozumi Rikuo}}\n:{{voiced by|Chikahiro Kobayashi}}<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-21/sing-yesterday-for-me-anime-reveals-cast-april-4-premiere/.155598|title=Sing 'Yesterday' for Me Anime Reveals Cast, April 4 Premiere|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 21, 2020|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n:Rikuo is a college graduate unsure about his future. He currently works at a convenience store. His hobby is photography. He has feelings for Shinako.\n;{{Nihongo|Haru Nonaka|\u91ce\u4e2d \u6674|Nonaka Haru}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Yume Miyamoto]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n:Haru is an eccentric girl working at MILK HALL. She adopted a crow and named it Kansuke. Because of the drastic change in her appearance, Rikuo does not remember meeting her five years ago. She often drops by the convenience store before going to work. \n;{{Nihongo|Shinako Morinome|\u68ee\u30ce\u76ee \u6980\u5b50|Morinome Shinako}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kana Hanazawa]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n:Shinako is Rikuo's classmate from college. She is currently working as a high school teacher. She is still in love with R\u014d's already deceased older brother. \n;{{Nihongo|R\u014d Hayakawa|\u65e9\u5ddd \u6d6a|Hayakawa R\u014d}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Natsuki Hanae]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n:R\u014d is Shinako's childhood friend from [[Kanazawa]].\n\n===Rikuo's Circle===\n;{{Nihongo|Kinoshita|\u6728\u30ce\u4e0b|Kinoshita}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Tatsuhisa Suzuki]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\">{{cite web|url=https://singyesterday.com/cast/|title=<nowiki>CAST / STAFF | TV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300e\u30a4\u30a8\u30b9\u30bf\u30c7\u30a4\u3092\u3046\u305f\u3063\u3066\u300f\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8</nowiki>|website=singyesterday.com|accessdate=February 19, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n:Rikuo's co-worker at a convenience store.\n;{{Nihongo|Takanori Fukuda|\u798f\u7530 \u30bf\u30ab\u30ce\u30ea|Fukuda Takanori}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Takuma Terashima]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Rikuo and Shinako's college classmate.\n;{{Nihongo|Kozue Fukuda|\u798f\u7530 \u68a2|Fukuda Kozue}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Aya Suzaki]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Tanakori's wife.\n;{{Nihongo|Chika Yuzuhara|\u67da\u539f \u30c1\u30ab|Yuzuhara Chika}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Eri Kitamura]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Rikuo's ex-girlfriend.\n\n===Haru's Circle===\n;{{Nihongo|Minato|\u6e4a|Minato}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u016bki Ono]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Haru's ex-classmate who has been in love with her.\n;{{Nihongo|Ky\u014dko Sayama|\u72ed\u5c71 \u674f\u5b50|Sayama Ky\u014dko}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Maaya Sakamoto]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Haru's employer. Owner of caf\u00e9 \"MILK HALL\".\n;{{Nihongo|Izawa|\u5c45\u6ca2|Izawa}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Maaya Sakamoto]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Ky\u014dko's high school classmate who's been in love with her.\n;{{Nihongo|Amamiya|\u96e8\u5bae|Amamiya}}\n:Has been in pursuit of Haru ever since meeting her at a Christmas party.\n;{{Nihongo|Mimori|\u307f\u3082\u308a|Mimori}}\n:Amamiya's childhood friend.\n;{{Nihongo|Y\u014dko Akimoto|\u79cb\u672c \u967d\u5b50|Akimoto Y\u014dko}}\n:Haru's birth mother.\n;{{Nihongo|Sh\u014dgo Kawashima|\u5ddd\u5cf6 \u7701\u543e|Kawashima Sh\u014dgo}}\n:Haru's step-father.\n;{{Nihongo|Kansuke|\u30ab\u30f3\u30b9\u30b1|Kansuke}}\n:{{voiced by|Ry\u014dko Maekawa}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Haru's pet crow.\n\n===Shinako's Circle===\n;{{Nihongo|Y\u016b Hayakawa|\u65e9\u5ddd \u6e67|Hayakawa Y\u016b}}\n:Shinako's childhood friend and R\u014d's brother. Died before the start of the series.\n;{{Nihongo|Morita|\u675c\u7530|Morita}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kaori Nazuka]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:Shinako's co-worker.\n;{{Nihongo|Takako Kinoshita|\u6728\u30ce\u4e0b \u697c\u5b50|Kinoshita Takako}}\n:Shinako's student and Kinoshita's sister.\n;{{Nihongo|Izumi Fukamachi|\u6df1\u753a \u6cc9|Fukamachi Izumi}}\n:Takako's classmate and president of the film club.\n\n===R\u014d's Circle===\n;{{Nihongo|Katsumi Takishita|\u6edd\u4e0b \u514b\u7f8e|Takishita Katsumi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Shun Horie]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n:R\u014d's classmate at prep school.\n;{{Nihongo|Rio|\u8389\u7dd2|Rio}}\n:A model working at R\u014d's prep school. At some point R\u014d's girlfriend.\n;{{Nihongo|Misato Kuzuhara|\u845b\u539f \u672a\u91cc|Kuzuhara Misato}}\n:R\u014d's classmate at prep school. Katsumi's target of affection.\n;{{Nihongo|Natsuki Nakahara|\u4e2d\u539f \u590f\u6a39|Nakahara Natsuki}}\n:R\u014d's classmate at prep school. Funatsuka's girlfriend.\n;{{Nihongo|Funatsuka|\u8239\u585a|Funatsuka}}\n:R\u014d's classmate at prep school. Natsuki's boyfriend.\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n\n===Anime===\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation was announced in the 10th issue of ''Grand Jump'' magazine on April 17, 2019.<ref name=\"ANN1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-12/kei-toume-sing-yesterday-for-me-manga-listed-with-tv-anime/.145625|title=Kei Toume's Sing 'Yesterday' for Me Manga Listed With TV Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 12, 2019|accessdate=April 17, 2019}}</ref>  The series is animated by [[Doga Kobo]] and directed by Yoshiyuki Fujiwara, with Fujiwara and Jin Tanaka writing the scripts and Junichir\u014d Taniguchi designing the characters.  DMM.futureworks is listed as producer. It premiered on April 4, 2020 on [[TV Asahi]]'s NUManimation block, [[AbemaTV]], and [[TV Asahi|BS Asahi]].<ref name=\"cast\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-19/sing-yesterday-for-me-anime-reveals-staff-visual-spring-2020-debut/.153480|title=Sing 'Yesterday' for Me Anime Reveals Staff, Visual, Spring 2020 Debut|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 19, 2019|accessdate=November 19, 2019}}</ref>  The series will run for 18 episodes, with the first 12 episodes airing on television and the last 6 episodes available through streaming on AbemaTV.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-21/sing-yesterday-for-me-anime-reveals-teaser-18-episode-length/.155626|title=Sing 'Yesterday' for Me Anime Reveals Teaser, 18-Episode Length|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 21, 2020|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\" style=\"width:98%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title<ref>{{cite web|url=https://singyesterday.com/story/|title=Story TV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300e\u30a4\u30a8\u30b9\u30bf\u30c7\u30a4\u3092\u3046\u305f\u3063\u3066\u300f\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate=April 5, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n!Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = The Outcasts of Society Aiming to Change Themselves\n| TranslitTitle       = Shakai no Hamidashisha wa jiko henkaku wo mezasu\n| NativeTitle         = \u793e\u4f1a\u306e\u306f\u307f\u51fa\u3057\u8005\u306f\u81ea\u5df1\u5909\u9769\u3092\u